					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>126 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>230</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>56</height>
										<width>87</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>126 folios (+ 1 unfoliated modern paper flyleaf at the beginning and 2 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of 8 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Water damage at edges in early leaves. </p>
									<p>Usage stains.
</p>
									<p>Slight worming at ends.
</p>
									<p>Marginalia in a fainter ink than main text. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="22" writtenLines="22">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible leaf by leaf hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Titles and inital words in larger characters. </p>
									<p>Catchwords from folio to folio.</p>
									<p>Marginal notes and additions throughout, in a different hand than the main text.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Sefardi semi-cursive script of the 15th century (main text); Yosef ha-Sofer Sefaradi: inscribed in the colophon, folio 123r. Sefardi semi-cursive script of the 16th century (marginalia).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
